<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,938,2007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,344,1298,1323]" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">Colouration</emphasis>
of the cuticle generally brown, meso- and metasternum dark brown, proximal half of femora black, rest of femora, tibiae, tarsi and antennae light brown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[825,932,1334,1359]" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">Vestiture</emphasis>
on head whitish with mixed yellowish setae, pronotum with yellowish setae complemented by whitish, with irregular small spots. Elytra mixed with brownish, yellowish and whitish, irregularly distributed setae, only vaguely forming coloured spots. Pronotum with a single central tuft of erect yellowish setae. Humeral part of elytra light, tubercles covered by short undistinguished brownish setae. Vestiture on antennae short, appressed, brownish. All legs covered by dense, fine brown setae, all femora light in distal part, tibiae with a wide dark strip bordered by two narrow indistinct whitish stripes. Lateral parts of venter of thorax and abdominal sternites with sparse and yellow-whitish pubescence.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,938,2007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,319,1586,1611]" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">Structure.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[331,391,1587,1611]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">Head</emphasis>
relatively short, rostrum flat and broad, without longitudinal carina (
<figureCitation box="[1211,1298,1586,1611]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 21" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[196,1373,204,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[185,1395,193,1935]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 21. Basidissus bendai sp. nov., female holotype: 15, head, dorsal view; 16, pronotum, lateral view, scheme; 17, proximal part of pronotum, dorsal view, scheme; 18, right antenna; 19, hemisternites, ventral view; 20, toothed plate with stylus, lateral view, seen in situ; 21, toothed plate, dorsal view, seen in situ. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285118/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">
Fig. 
<number box="[1268,1298,1586,1611]" pageId="1" pageNumber="72" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
), only with inconspicuous median depression, ratio of rostrum length to maximum width 
<number box="[1047,1100,1622,1647]" pageId="1" pageNumber="72" value="0.63">0.63</number>
. Scrobes not visible dorsally, scape slightly hidden in scrobe in dorsal view. Eyes large, convex, ocular index 
<number box="[1080,1132,1659,1683]" pageId="1" pageNumber="72" value="1.94">1.94</number>
. Ratio of maximum width across eyes to maximum width of rostrum 
<number box="[652,704,1695,1719]" pageId="1" pageNumber="72" value="1.49">1.49</number>
. Antennae (
<figureCitation box="[845,929,1694,1719]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 21" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[196,1373,204,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[185,1395,193,1935]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 21. Basidissus bendai sp. nov., female holotype: 15, head, dorsal view; 16, pronotum, lateral view, scheme; 17, proximal part of pronotum, dorsal view, scheme; 18, right antenna; 19, hemisternites, ventral view; 20, toothed plate with stylus, lateral view, seen in situ; 21, toothed plate, dorsal view, seen in situ. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285118/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">
Fig. 
<number box="[901,929,1695,1719]" pageId="1" pageNumber="72" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
) reaching to posterior margin of pronotum. Funicle thin, club robust. 
<emphasis box="[466,577,1731,1754]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">Pronotum</emphasis>
transverse, ratio of length to width at carina 
<number box="[1141,1193,1730,1755]" pageId="1" pageNumber="72" value="0.69">0.69</number>
, gradually narrowed anteriorly, widest at dorsal transverse carina. Dorsal transverse carina very slightly bisinuate (
<figureCitation box="[1218,1302,1766,1791]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 21" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[196,1373,204,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[185,1395,193,1935]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 21. Basidissus bendai sp. nov., female holotype: 15, head, dorsal view; 16, pronotum, lateral view, scheme; 17, proximal part of pronotum, dorsal view, scheme; 18, right antenna; 19, hemisternites, ventral view; 20, toothed plate with stylus, lateral view, seen in situ; 21, toothed plate, dorsal view, seen in situ. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285118/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">
Fig. 
<number box="[1272,1302,1767,1791]" pageId="1" pageNumber="72" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
), convex in the middle. Lateral carina only slightly emarginate in dorsal view terminating in half of pronotum length (
<figureCitation box="[1346,1427,1802,1827]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 21" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[196,1373,204,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[185,1395,193,1935]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 21. Basidissus bendai sp. nov., female holotype: 15, head, dorsal view; 16, pronotum, lateral view, scheme; 17, proximal part of pronotum, dorsal view, scheme; 18, right antenna; 19, hemisternites, ventral view; 20, toothed plate with stylus, lateral view, seen in situ; 21, toothed plate, dorsal view, seen in situ. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285118/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">
Fig. 
<number box="[1398,1427,1802,1827]" pageId="1" pageNumber="72" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
) Dorsal transverse carina in contact with lateral carina right-angled from dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[1105,1188,1838,1863]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 21" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[196,1373,204,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[185,1395,193,1935]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 21. Basidissus bendai sp. nov., female holotype: 15, head, dorsal view; 16, pronotum, lateral view, scheme; 17, proximal part of pronotum, dorsal view, scheme; 18, right antenna; 19, hemisternites, ventral view; 20, toothed plate with stylus, lateral view, seen in situ; 21, toothed plate, dorsal view, seen in situ. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285118/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">
Fig. 
<number box="[1157,1188,1839,1863]" pageId="1" pageNumber="72" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,938,2007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis box="[199,269,1875,1899]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">Elytra</emphasis>
broadly suboval (
<figureCitation box="[471,537,1874,1899]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1940,1963]" captionTargetBox="[175,1415,230,1926]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[175,1417,195,1934]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Madagascan Basidissus species, dorsal view, 1, B. bendai sp. nov., female holotype (3.0 mm); 2, B. cirrifer Frieser, 2000 (7.2 mm); 3, B. cristatus Fairmaire, 1897 (4.9 mm); 4, B. fulvitarsis Frieser, 2007 (4.6 mm); 5, B. incilis Frieser, 2000 (6.1 mm); 6, B. senilis Frieser, 2000 (6.5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285115/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">
Fig. 
<number box="[524,537,1875,1899]" pageId="1" pageNumber="72" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
), narrowed in distal third of their length. Ratio of the maximum length of elytra to maximum width 
<number box="[380,432,1910,1935]" pageId="1" pageNumber="72" value="1.16">1.16</number>
. 
<emphasis box="[445,551,1910,1934]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">Abdomen</emphasis>
shorter than broad (
